'''西伯利亞野牛'''（學名：''Bison priscus''），又名'''草原野牛'''，是生存於[[第四紀|第四紀]][[歐洲|歐洲]]<ref name=Europe>[http://www.kirmuseum.ru/issue/guide/detail.php?ID=3055 Вестник Кирилло-Белозерского музея 9 (Май 2006) О. Яшина, Т.В. Цветкова – Кирилловский бизон] {{Wayback|url=http://www.kirmuseum.ru/issue/guide/detail.php?ID=3055 |date=20171015202137 }}. Kirmuseum.ru. Retrieved on 2013-05-31.</ref>、[[中亞|中亞]]<ref name=Asia>{{cite journal |last=Vasiliev |first=S. K. |year=2008 |title=Late pleistocene bison (''Bison p. priscus'' Bojanis, 1827) from the Southeastern part of Western Siberia |journal=Archaeology, Ethnology and Anthropology of Eurasia |doi=10.1016/j.aeae.2008.07.004 |volume=34 |issue=2 |pages=34–56}}</ref>、[[北亞|北亞]]<ref name=OushuCattle>{{cite journal |last=Kurosawa |first=Y. |title=モノが語る牛と人間の文化 -　② 岩手の牛たち |publisher={{link-ja|奥州市牛の博物館}} |journal=LIAJ News |number=109 |pages=29–31 |url=http://liaj.lin.gr.jp/japanese/liajnews/liaj10909.pdf |format=pdf |accessdate=2016-04-06 |archive-date=2016-04-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160419105413/http://liaj.lin.gr.jp/japanese/liajnews/liaj10909.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=KuzuuFossil>{{cite journal |last1=Hasegawa |first1=Y. |last2=Okumura |first2=Y. |last3=Tatsukawa |first3=H. |year=2009 |title=First record of Late Pleistocene Bison from the fissure deposits of the Kuzuu Limestone, Yamasuge，Sano-shi，Tochigi Prefecture，Japan |journal=Bull.Gunma Mus.Natu.Hist. |publisher=Gunma Museum of Natural History and Kuzuu Fossil Museum |number=13 |pages=47–52 |url=http://www.gmnh.pref.gunma.jp/research/no_13/bulletin13_5.pdf |format=pdf |accessdate=2016-04-06 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924022657/http://www.gmnh.pref.gunma.jp/research/no_13/bulletin13_5.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |year=2016 |title=The Yukagir Bison: The exterior morphology of a complete frozen mummy of the extinct steppe bison, Bison priscus from the early Holocene of northern Yakutia, Russia |journal=Quaternary International |last1=Boeskorov |first1=Gennady G. |last2=Potapova |first2=Olga R. |last3=Protopopov |first3=Albert V. |last4=Plotnikov |first4=Valery V. |last5=Agenbroad |first5=Larry D. |last6=Kirikov |first6=Konstantin S. |last7=Pavlov |first7=Innokenty S. |last8=Shchelchkova |first8=Marina V. |last9=Belolyubskii |first9=Innocenty N. |last10=Tomshin |first10=Mikhail D. |last11=Kowalczyk |first11=Rafal |last12=Davydov |first12=Sergey P. |last13=Kolesov |first13=Stanislav D. |last14=Tikhonov |first14=Alexey N. |last15=Van Der Plicht |first15=Johannes |doi=10.1016/j.quaint.2015.11.084 |volume=406 |pages=94–110}}</ref>、[[白令陸橋|白令陸橋]]及[[北美洲|北美洲]]<ref name="Pleisto">{{cite journal |last1=Zazula |first1=Grant D. |last2=MacKay |first2=Glen |last3=Andrews |first3=Thomas D. |last4=Shapiro |first4=Beth |authorlink4=Beth Shapiro |last5=Letts |first5=Brandon |last6=Broc |first6=Fiona |year=2009 |title=A late Pleistocene steppe bison (''Bison priscus'') partial carcass from Tsiigehtchic, Northwest Territories, Canada |journal=Quaternary Science Reviews |doi=10.1016/j.quascirev.2009.06.012 |volume=28 |issue=25–26 |pages=2734–2742}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Marsolier-Kergoat |first1=Marie-Claude |last2=Palacio |first2=Pauline |last3=Berthonaud |first3=Véronique |last4=Maksud |first4=Frédéric |last5=Stafford |first5=Thomas |last6=Bégouën |first6=Robert |last7=Elalouf |first7=Jean-Marc |date=2015-06-17 |title=Hunting the Extinct Steppe Bison (Bison priscus) Mitochondrial Genome in the Trois-Frères Paleolithic Painted Cave |journal=PLOS ONE |doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0128267 |issn=1932-6203 |pmc=4471230 |pmid=26083419 |volume=10 |issue=6 |pages=e0128267 |url=http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0128267 |access-date=2020-09-18 |archive-date=2017-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516174738/http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0128267 |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[加拿大|加拿大]]至[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]地區[[草原|草原]]上的野牛。该生物现已灭绝，有時會出現在[[石洞壁畫|石洞壁畫]]中。

==演化==
[[Image:Steppe_Bison.jpg|thumb]] 
[[File:Prazubr_rysunek_600.jpg|thumb]]
西伯利亞野牛有可能是在[[南亞|南亞]]進行[[演化|演化]]。由於牠們生活的時間及地方與[[原牛|原牛]]相同，故有時會把牠的後裔與原牛混淆。

於[[全新世|全新世]][[滅絕|滅絕]]。在歐洲，牠們是被現今的[[歐洲野牛|歐洲野牛]]所取代；而在美洲，牠們則是被[[美洲野牛|美洲野牛]]與其他同屬野牛（包括[[古風野牛|古風野牛]]、[[長角野牛|長角野牛]]以及{{link-en|福爾松野牛|Bison occidentalis}}）所取代。

西伯利亞野牛超過2米高，像現今的美洲野牛。兩角角尖相距約1米，角本身亦長約半米。其體重可達{{convert|900|kg}}。<ref>McPhee, R. D. E. (1999) ''Extinctions in Near Time: Causes, Contexts, and Consequences'', Springer, isbn 0306460920, p. 262.</ref>

==發現==

西伯利亞野牛出現在[[石洞壁畫|石洞壁畫]]之中，尤其是在[[阿爾塔米拉洞|阿爾塔米拉洞]]以及[[拉斯科洞窟壁畫|拉斯科洞窟]]中。其他形式的[[史前藝術|史前藝術]]包括由馴鹿角雕刻而成的{{link-en|Bison Licking Insect Bite}}。另外也有發現許多冰凍的西伯利亞野牛屍體<ref name=evolution>{{cite journal|title=Maternal and Paternal Lineages in Cross-Breeding Bovine Species. Has Wisent a Hybrid Origin? |doi=10.1093/molbev/msh064|year=2004|last1=Verkaar|first1=E. L. C.|journal=Molecular Biology and Evolution|volume=21|issue=7|pages=1165–70|pmid=14739241|last2=Nijman|first2=IJ|last3=Beeke|first3=M|last4=Hanekamp|first4=E|last5=Lenstra|first5=JA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=8ikKezOKRB4C&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false | title = Frozen Fauna of the Mammoth Steppe: The Story of Blue Babe | ISBN = 9780226311234 | author1 = Dale Guthrie | first1 = R | date = 1989}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Paglia | first1 = C. | year = 2004 | title = The Magic of Images: Word and Picture in a Media Age | journal = Arion: A Journal of Humanities and the Classics | volume = 11 | issue = 3 | pages = 1–22 | publisher = Trustees of Boston University | jstor = 20163935 | doi = 10.2307/20163935}}</ref>。

在1979年7月，一具36,000年前的雄性西伯利亞野牛[[木乃伊|木乃伊]]在[[美國|美國]][[費爾班克斯_(阿拉斯加州)|費爾班克斯]]發現，被暱稱為 '''Blue Babe''' （意思為「藍寶貝」）。這具木乃伊由當地的一名[[金礦開採|金礦工]]發現，同時也是 '''Blue Babe''' 的命名者，"Babe" 一詞來自於[[美國神話|美國神話]]中[[保羅·班揚|保羅·班揚]]身旁同名的藍色公牛。木乃伊呈現藍色的原因主要是因為整個樣本表層覆蓋著一層{{link-en|藍鐵礦|vivianite}}<ref name=priscus>[http://www.beringia.com/research/bison.html "Steppe Bison"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.beringia.com/research/bison.html |date=20101212134450 }} – Yukon Beringia Interpretive Centre. Beringia.com. Retrieved on 2013-05-31.</ref>。{{link-en|北方極地博物館|University of Alaska Museum of the North}}
的研究團隊在將這具木乃伊放入博物館進行永久展示之前，移除了部分頸肉，烹調後食用以慶祝這項特別的發現<ref>{{Cite journal | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=cuQhsNQcKMYC&lpg=PA169&dq=neck%20isbn%3A0226311236&pg=PA298#v=onepage&q&f=false | title = Frozen Fauna of the Mammoth Steppe: The Story of Blue Babe | ISBN = 9780226311234 | author1 = Dale Guthrie | first1 = R | date = 1989 | p=298}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=ḎḤWTY|title=Blue Babe: Would You Eat 36,000-year-old Bison Meat?|url=http://www.ancient-origins.net/artifacts-other-artifacts/blue-babe-would-you-eat-36000-year-old-bison-meat-009862|website=Ancient Origins|accessdate=8 April 2018|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201004161801/https://www.ancient-origins.net/artifacts-other-artifacts/blue-babe-would-you-eat-36000-year-old-bison-meat-009862|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

在2011年7月，一具9,300年前的西伯利亞野牛木乃伊發現於西伯利亞{{link-en|尤卡吉爾|Yukagir}}地區<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livescience.com/48653-bison-mummy-brains-organs.html|title=9,000-Year-Old Bison Mummy Found Frozen in Time|last=Palermo|first=Elizabeth|date=6 November 2014|publisher=www.livescience.com|accessdate=4 December 2014|archive-date=2020-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219045527/https://www.livescience.com/48653-bison-mummy-brains-organs.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

